						<img id="m" src="Minerva McGonagall.jpg"/>
						Minerva McGonagall.<br/>
						Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Master Griffindor and Professor of Transfigurations.<br/>
						It is one of only seven Animagus officially registered this century. The animal that can transform is the cat.
						Learn about transformation theory and order. To be exact, you will learn transformation as a common subject until fifth grade, and then you will learn transformation in advanced courses after sixth grade.
					</h4>
				</div><br/>

				<div>
					<h4>
						<h3>Flights</h3>
						<img id="r" src="Rolanda Hooch.jpg"/>
						Rolanda Hooch.<br/>
						He is a flight drill professor at Hogwarts.<br/> 
						For some reason, unlike other professors, she is called Mrs. Hochi, not Professor Hochi.<br/> 
						It is an outdoor class, subject that I only learn in the first grade. It is a subject that corresponds to physical education in the Muggle world.<br/>
						He is also in charge of referees in the Quidditch competition between dormitories.
					</h4>
				</div><br/>

				<div>
					<h4>
						<h3>Herbology</h3>
						<img id="p" src="herbal_professor.png"/>
						Pomona Sprout.<br/>
						Hogwarts Professor of Herbology.<br/>
						Learn about many magical plants and how to handle them. 
						Along with aeronautical skills, they usually have outdoor classes in their greenhouse. Due to the nature of the subject, it is highly relevant to magic medicine classes.
					</h4>
				</div><br/>

				<div>
